At SPP’s minimum perihelion, the Sun cannot be considered as a point source. SPP utilizes this aspect in the design of the solar arrays, exposing part of the solar arrays to only a fraction of the Sun (penumbra) at perihelion and protecting the remainder of the solar arrays in the umbra. This approach, along with the nearly 70∘\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
