Protecting SPP from the harsh solar environment has been a primary design driver from the initial conception of the mission, and includes the following: 
The TPS coating and TPS foam thickness are sized to nearly eliminate the heat flow to the spacecraft and instruments from the 475 Suns environment closest approach, enabling the majority of SPP components and instruments to operate in a near standard spacecraft thermal environment.
